<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-14T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-14T05:00:00-05:00" n="668" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5112 France/20: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-14T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">June 14,
                                        1927—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 14—7:27
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>248. As Briand is at Geneva, I conveyed orally to Berthelot<note n="4" xml:id="d668fn4">Secretary General of the French Ministry of Foreign
                                Affairs.</note> substance of your telegram No. 174, June 11, 11
                            a.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>